{META_DATA}: FADE IN:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 1 INT. DERELICT HOUSE - DAY <<COLOUR SEQUENCE>>
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A POLAROID PHOTOGRAPH, clasped between finger and thumb: a crude, crime scene flash picture of a MAN'S BODY lying on a decaying wooden floor, a BLOODY MESS where his head should be.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The image in the photo starts to FADE as we SUPER TITLES.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The hand holding the photo suddenly FANS it in a rapid FLAPPING motion, then holds it still.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The image fades more, and again the picture is FANNED.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: As TITLES END the image fades to nothing.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The hand holding the photo FLAPS it again, then places it at the front of a POLAROID CAMERA.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The camera SUCKS the blank picture up, then the FLASH BURSTS.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The Polaroid camera is lowered, revealing the sweaty, heavy- breathing face of LEONARD (mid-30's).
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: There are droplets of blood across his face.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Leonard stares, satisfied, at something on the ground in front of him.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: There is WET BLOOD on his BLUE SHIRT and BEIGE SUIT.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: His hand opens and catches a HANDGUN which leaps up into his grasp.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Still staring, he crouches down and pulls a BODY off the floor by the wet hair of its BLOODY HEAD.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He slowly inserts the barrel of the gun into the bloody mess where the mouth should be.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Leonard FLINCHES.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A DEAFENING ROAR as wet red leaps off his face and suit and head, with a SPASM, reassembles itself into the face of TEDDY (40's, moustache) and we-
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 2 INT. MOTEL ROOM 21 - DAY ##BLACK AND WHITE SEQUENCE##
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Close on Leonard's eyes.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He rolls them to one side, then turns his head.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: LEONARD (V.O.)
{DIALOGUE}: So where are you?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Leonard lifts his head.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He is lying on a queen-sized bed.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: LEONARD (cont'd)
{DIALOGUE}: You're in some motel room.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{META_DATA}: 2.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 3 EXT. DERELICT BUILDING - DAY <<COLOUR SEQUENCE>>
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A late model Jaguar bumps across some railroad tracks and approaches a large, clearly abandoned DERELICT BUILDING.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Leonard is driving.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He wears a BEIGE SUIT and BLUE SHIRT (no blood).
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Next to him is TEDDY.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Leonard stops the car next to a PICKUP TRUCK sitting Outside the derelict building.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Leonard kills the engine, staring at the pickup.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: LEONARD
{DIALOGUE}: Looks like somebody's home.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Teddy looks from Leonard to the pickup and back.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: TEDDY
{DIALOGUE}: That thing's been here for years.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Leonard gets out of the Jaguar and moves to the pickup.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He inspects it with a methodical, practiced eye.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Teddy follows.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: LEONARD
{DIALOGUE}: I think you're wrong.
{DIALOGUE}: These tracks aren't more than a few days old.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Leonard opens the door of the pickup and searches the interior.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: On the dirty vinyl of the passenger seat he finds six BULLETS.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Leonard picks two of them up and studies them.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He drops them onto the dashboard then SHUTS the door.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: LEONARD (cont'd)
{DIALOGUE}: Let's take a look inside.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Leonard walks towards the house, patting his jacket pockets.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Teddy leans on the pickup, uneasy, watching Leonard.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 4 INT. DERELICT BUILDING - DAY <<COLOUR SEQUENCE>>
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Leonard stands in the dimly-lit, decaying former hallway.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He pulls a stack of POLAROID PHOTOGRAPHS out of his pocket and leafs through them as Teddy starts walking towards him.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Leonard finds a photo showing Teddy with a shit-eating grin standing in front of the pickup truck.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: On the broad white strip beneath the photo is handwritten:
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: "TEDDY GAMMELL TEL. 555 0134"
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Leonard flips the photo over.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: On the white strip on the back, in the same small handwriting.
{META_DATA}: (CONTINUED)
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: MEMENTO Pink Revisions - 9/7/99
{META_DATA}: 3.
{META_DATA}: 4 CONTINUED:
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: "DON'T LISTEN TO HIS LIES"
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: "HE IS THE ONE"
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: "KILL HIM"
{CHARACTER_NAME}: LEONARD (V.0.)
{DIALOGUE}: I've finally found him.
{DIALOGUE}: How long have I been looking?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Leonard stuffs the Polaroids back into his pocket, reaches around to the back of his waistband and draws a HANDGUN, keeping it out of Teddy's line of sight.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Teddy enters, wary.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: TEDDY
{DIALOGUE}: Find anything?
{DIALOGUE}: Didn't think so, let's go, yeah?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Leonard neither replies nor turns around.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Teddy, worried, affects a casual air, shrugging dismissively,
{CHARACTER_NAME}: TEDDY (cont'd)
{DIALOGUE}: Fuck this.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Teddy turns and heads for the door.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Leonard LEAPS on him, pistol-whipping him furiously as he shouts:
{CHARACTER_NAME}: LEONARD
{DIALOGUE}: YOU PAY FOR WHAT YOU DID!
{DIALOGUE}: YOU BEG FORGIVENESS, THEN YOU PAY!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Teddy is down.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Leonard DRAGS him back, deeper into the dark house.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Leonard is in a frenzy.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He dumps Teddy at the end of the hall and stands over him.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Teddy SPITS BLOOD.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: TEDDY
{DIALOGUE}: You don't have a clue, you freak.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Leonard crouches down and grabs Teddy by the lapels.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: LEONARD
{DIALOGUE}: Beg my forgiveness!
{DIALOGUE}: Beg my wife's forgiveness before I blow your brains out!
{CHARACTER_NAME}: TEDDY
{DIALOGUE}: Leonard, you don't have a clue what's going on.
{DIALOGUE}: You don't even know my name.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: LEONARD
{META_DATA}: (triumphant smile)
{DIALOGUE}: Teddy!
{META_DATA}: (CONTINUED)
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: MEMENTO Pink Revisions - 9/7/99 3A.
{META_DATA}: 4 CONTINUED: (2)
