{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He is awkward and uncomfortable.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He notices an ICE BUCKET by the sink.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 16 INT. MOTEL ROOM 21 - DAY ##BLACK AND WHITE SEQUENCE##
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Leonard sits on the bed applying SHAVING FOAM to his thigh.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The ICE BUCKET sits on the bedside table, steaming.
{META_DATA}: (CONTINUED)
{META_DATA}: 12.
{META_DATA}: 16 CONTINUED:
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Leonard starts awkwardly SHAVING his right thigh.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The PHONE RINGS and Leonard FLINCHES, NICKING his leg.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He looks at the phone, then reaches for the receiver.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 17 INT. A RESTAURANT RESTROOM - DAY <<COLOUR SEQUENCE>>
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Leonard, in BEIGE SUIT and BLUE SHIRT flushes the urinal, then moves to the sink and starts washing his hands.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He notices a MESSAGE written on the back of his hand.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: "REMEMBER SAMMY JANKIS"
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He stares at the message for a second, thoughtful, then tries to scrub the writing off his skin.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: To his surprise, it is INDELIBLE.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Leonard looks at it, quizzical, then notices some markings on his wrist, pulling his sleeve back to get a better look.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He can read the start of a message:
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: "THE FACTS:"
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Leonard is about to roll his sleeve up further when the restroom door opens and a MAN enters.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Leonard dries his hands, then exits the rest room.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 18 INT. RESTAURANT - DAY <<COLOUR SEQUENCE>>
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Leonard emerges .
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: nto the waiting area of a crowded restaurant.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He glances around, lost, then pulls out his Polaroids, flipping through them.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Someone taps him on his shoulder and he turns to see the smiling face of a waiter.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: WAITER
{DIALOGUE}: Sir?
{DIALOGUE}: You left these at your table.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Leonard looks down.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The waiter hands him a BROWN ENVELOPE and a MOTEL ROOM KEY (DISCOUNT INN, ROOM 304).
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: On the envelope is a handwritten message:
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: "FOR LEONARD, FROM NATALIE"
