{META_DATA}: (listens)
{DIALOGUE}: She knew that I was the one who had built he case for Sammy faking it.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 118 INT. LEONARD'S OFFICE - DAY ##BLACK AND WHITE SEQUENCE##
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Leonard, in a CHEAP SUIT AND TIE, gets up from behind his desk to shake hands with Mrs. Jankis.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They talk, Leonard nodding as he listens.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Mrs. Jankis is crying.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: LEONARD (V.O.)
{DIALOGUE}: She told me about life with Sammy, how she'd treated him.
{DIALOGUE}: It had got to the point where she'd get Sammy to hide food all around the house, then stop feeding him to see if his hunger would make him remember where he'd hidden the stuff.
{DIALOGUE}: She wasn't a cruel person, she just wanted her old Sammy back.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The tearful Mrs. Jankis gives Leonard a determined look.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MRS. JANKIS
{DIALOGUE}: Mr. Shelby, you know all about Sammy and you decided that he was faking -
{CHARACTER_NAME}: LEONARD
{DIALOGUE}: Mrs. Jankis, the company's position isn't that Sammy is "faking" anything, just that his condition can't be shown -
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MRS. JANKIS
