{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She sets her watch back by fifteen minutes.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MRS. JANKIS
{DIALOGUE}: Sammy, it's time for my shot.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Sammy looks up, smiling, glad to be able to help.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He goes into the kitchen and comes back with the bottle of insulin, the syringe and a new cotton swab.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He carefully prepares the injection and Mrs. Jankis offers him her other arm.
